notes.text:
The file fep4.19 was obtained from http://homepages.ed.ac.uk/graeme/moldy/moldy.html and posted with the permission of G.J. Ackland. Besides the parameterized functions in the file, there are also some calculated quantities useful as confirmation.
From that website: "The iron potential here is slightly improved from the 2003 version to eliminate negative thermal expansion. It has a melting point of 1796 K."
